                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"We are given the sides of the two legs and are asked to find the length of the hypotenuse. To do this we must use the Pythagorean Theorem, where "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"a^2 + b^2 = c^2"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". First we set up the equation "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"153.3^2 + 69^2 = c^2"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". We get "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"23500.89 + 4761 = c^2"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", then when we add the two numbers on the LHS we get "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"28261.89 = c^2"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". To get the value of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"c"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", we must square root both sides of the equation so "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"168.112730036 = c"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". The question said to round up the answer to the tenth place so "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"168.1 = c"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"While "},{"type":"text","text":"Red","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is definitely the right answer once the system comes to rest, "},{"type":"text","text":"Blue","marks":[{"type":"bold"}]},{"type":"text","text":" can hold more water for a short period of time.  You can fill it all the way to the top.  The water will run out until it reaches the level of the top of the spout, but for some period of time it will hold more than the Red can."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The length and height of spout of red can is more as compare to blue can. so red can hold more water"}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Because of how liquids occupy space the water is limited to the height of the tip of the spout. The red spout is considerably higher assuming the cans are the same distance away from the viewer. This means that the red pot (in this position) will hold more water."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It depends on what your definition of 'holds' is. Indeed the red can will fill to a higher level assuming that the quantity of the water filling the cans is not more than the quantity of water exiting the spout or that the flow of water has stopped after the cans have reached capacity. If the water is at a higher intake than outtake of water then it is safe to assume that, if the water intake is consistent, the blue will hold more water than the red can."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Volume in this case is dictated by the height of the end of the spout, not the height of the container."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"It's a issue of equilibrium. The spout of the red can is bigger than that of the blue one, but it is also longer and higher. Therefore, more water pressure is need to push the water through the spout. Meaning: More water is required to push the water through the spout of the red can than through the blue can. The red can will hold more water before it starts to lose water."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"the water spout for the red can is higher , and thus the water will equalize at a higher level between the main tank and the water spout. Whereas the blue water can the spout is lower and only water to that level can accumulate in the blue can, before it drains out of the spout."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"If radius of both the container are similar, the level of water in a container is determined on the basis of orifice (outlet). The distance from the base to the orifice is larger in the red can compared to the blue can. In short, higher the outlet or spout is, there will be more volume available to hold liquids."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The blue although taller in size the sprout will leak out a large volume of water as it is much lower than the red."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The red one by the principle of communicating vessels. The jet of irrigation is higher than the one of the blue therefore if it is less high it will be able to maintain more water in its interior in vertical position"}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}

{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"




                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The level of the spout is the maximum resting volume of either can. The red can's spout is higher, with the same diameter, yielding a larger volume than the blue can."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



                            "}]}
